3 Treemap

tm <-  treemap(
   GNI2014,
   index = c("continent", "iso3"),
   vSize = "population",
   vColor = "GNI",
   type = "value",
   draw = F
)

6 Case 2

n <- 300
df <- data.frame(index1 = sample(c("PC", "Mobile", "Tablet"), n, replace = TRUE),
                 index2 = paste0("Visit", sample(1:10, n, replace = TRUE)),
                 val = sample(5:30, n, replace = TRUE)) %>%
  mutate(ord = as.numeric(factor(index1, levels = c("PC","Mobile","Tablet"), labels = c(1,2,3))))

str(df)
## 'data.frame':    300 obs. of  4 variables:
##  $ index1: Factor w/ 3 levels "Mobile","PC",..: 3 2 2 3 3 3 1 3 2 2 ...
##  $ index2: Factor w/ 10 levels "Visit1","Visit10",..: 8 3 6 5 9 5 9 4 6 8 ...
##  $ val   : int  11 16 5 6 17 8 13 16 7 10 ...
##  $ ord   : num  3 1 1 3 3 3 2 3 1 1 ...
d3tree2(
  treemap(df, 
          index = c("index1","index2"),
          vSize = "val",
          algorithm = "pivotSize",
          palette = colorRampPalette(c("#f94560", "#a87963", "#4b61ba"))(length(unique(df[, 1]))))
  , rootname = "TEST"
)

d3tree(
  treemap(df, 
          index = c("index1","index2"),
          vSize = "val",
          type = "index",
          format.legend = list(scientific = FALSE, big.mark = " "),
          algorithm = "pivotSize",
          fontsize.labels = 20,
          fontsize.legend = 20,
          inflate.labels = T,
          sortID = "ord",
          eval.labels = T,
          force.print.labels = T,
          palette = colorRampPalette(c("#f94560", "#a87963", "#4b61ba"))(length(unique(df[, 1]))))
  ,rootname = "GROUP"
  ,celltext = "name"
)
